@member

Syntax

@member [{<data_type>}] <name>

Overview

This tag marks a symbol as a member of enclosing scope (class or object). It is equivalent to using the @name and @type tags together.

Example(s)

class Document {
  /**
   * The identifier for this node.
   * 
   * @member {string} id
   */
}
